Package: pigworld
Title: Agent-Based Ecological Model of Pigs on an Infinite 2D Plane
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("miniextendr", "authors", , "miniextendr@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: An agent-based ecological simulation of pigs roaming an infinite
    2D plane. Features birth and death processes, Gaussian random-walk movement,
    pairwise interaction within a configurable radius, and energy-based
    reproduction. Implemented in Rust via miniextendr for performance, using
    rand/rand_distr for stochastic processes, rayon for parallel computation,
    and itertools for data aggregation.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
